# Development Workflow

## Quick Reference

```bash
cargo build --workspace                                        # Build all crates
cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1                     # Run all tests (always single-threaded)
cargo run --manifest-path crates/u-forge-core/Cargo.toml --example cli_demo   # Run CLI demo
cargo run --manifest-path crates/u-forge-core/Cargo.toml --example cli_demo ./data.json ./schemas/  # Custom data
```

> **No `source env.sh` required.** Bundled SQLite compiles with any standard C compiler on PATH.

---

## First Time Setup

1. **Install prerequisites:**
   - Rust stable toolchain — [rustup.rs](https://rustup.rs)
   - A C compiler (`gcc`, `clang`, or MSVC) — needed only for `openssl-sys` (reqwest TLS)
   - *(Optional)* [Lemonade Server](https://github.com/lemonade-sdk/lemonade) for semantic embeddings

2. **Build:**
   ```bash
   cargo build --workspace   # ~30 seconds first time (bundled SQLite compilation)
   ```

3. **Run tests:**
   ```bash
   cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1   # All 220+ tests pass with no server required
   ```

4. **Run the CLI demo:**
   ```bash
   cargo run --manifest-path crates/u-forge-core/Cargo.toml --example cli_demo
   ```

